    <div xml:id="PN237">
      <lg type="edition">
<l>nīṭuvāḻ keṉṟiyā ṉeṭuṅkaṭai kuṟukip</l>
<l>pāṭi niṉṟa pacināṭ kaṇṇē</l>
<l>kōṭaik kālattuk koḻuniḻa lākip</l>
<l>poytta laṟiyā vuravōṉ cevimutal</l>
<l>vittiya paṉuval viḷaintaṉṟu naṉṟeṉa</l>
<l>nacci yirunta nacaipaḻu tāka</l>
<l>vaṭṭa kuḻici yaḻaṟpayan tāaṅ</l>
<l>kaḷiyar tāmē yārka veṉṉā</l>
<l>vaṟaṉil kūṟṟan tiṟaṉiṉṟu tuṇiya</l>
<l>vūḻi ṉuruppa verukkiya makaḷir</l>
<l>vāḻai pūviṉ vaḷaimuṟi citaṟa</l>
<l>mutuvā yokkaṟ paricila riraṅkak</l>
<l>kaḷḷi pōkiya kaḷariyam paṟantalai</l>
<l>veḷvēl viṭalai ceṉṟumāyn taṉaṉē</l>
<l>yāṅkatu nōyiṉ ṟāka vōṅkuvaraip</l>
<l>pulipārt toṟṟiya kaḷiṟṟirai piḻaippi</l>
<l>ṉelipārt toṟṟā tāku malitiraik</l>
<l>kaṭaṉmaṇṭu puṉali ṉiḻumeṉac ceṉṟu</l>
<l>naṉiyuṭaip pariciṟ ṟaruka</l>
<l>meḻumati neñcē tuṇipumun tuṟuttē.</l>
</lg>
<lg type="translation" xml:lang="en">
<l>On a day of hunger when I stood singing, (2)</l>
<l>having approached the tall gate saying “may he live long”, (1)</l>
<l>longing that, (6a)</l>
<l>there being fat shade in the time of the west wind, (3)</l>
<l>the composition sown into the ear of a strong man</l>
<l>who does not know of lying will well bear fruit, (4f.)</l>
<l>  since the longing that existed was false, (6b-d)</l>
<l>as if the pot that cooked yielded [only] fire, (7)</l>
<l>since virtuless Death today decided the matter, (9)</l>
<l>not saying “pitiable they are. Let them eat.” (8)</l>
<l>while women that are burningly harrasses in turn (10)</l>
<l>scatter broken pieces of bangles, like plantain flowers, (11)</l>
<l>While mendicants with [their] old-mouthed kinfolk are in grief, (12)</l>
<l>the warrior with a white spear has gone [and] vanished (14)</l>
<l>in the wasteland with saline soil where spurges have grown long. (13)</l>
<l>While that thus is without pain, if a tiger on the high mountain</l>
<l>fails [to have as its] prey the elephant bull which  it hasve peered out at [and] attacked, (15f.)</l>
<l>it will not peer at [and] attack a rat. (17a-c)</l>
<l>Going sweetly like the flood that rushes in the sea with amply waves (17d-18)</l>
<l>we will bring ample(?) gifts. (19)</l>
<l>Rise, o heart, putting you resolve first.  </l>
</lg>
